<!-- ===== How it works ===== -->
<section class="section" id="how" style="padding-bottom:36px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> How it works</span>
      <h2>Three steps from live site to local folder.</h2>
      <p>Under the hood we run a finely-tuned <code>wget</code> mirror, rewrite every link for offline use, then stream the result straight to your browser.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="features">
      <article class="card" data-reveal>
        <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m21 21-4.34-4.34"/><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="8"/></svg></div>
        <h3>1 · Paste a URL</h3>
        <p>Drop in any address. We resolve the host and begin a recursive crawl that follows internal links page by page.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card" data-reveal>
        <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2v20"/><path d="m17 5-5-3-5 3"/><path d="m17 19-5 3-5-3"/><path d="M2 12h20"/></svg></div>
        <h3>2 · Watch it mirror</h3>
        <p>A live console streams real <code>wget</code> output — files counted, progress tracked — so you see exactly what lands on disk.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card" data-reveal>
        <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15v4a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-4"/><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5"/><path d="M12 15V3"/></svg></div>
        <h3>3 · Grab the ZIP</h3>
        <p>Everything is compressed and handed back as one archive. Unzip, open <code>index.html</code>, and browse fully offline.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== Features ===== -->
<section class="section" id="features" style="padding-top:0">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="features">
      <article class="card" data-reveal>
        <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M4 4h16v16H4z"/><path d="M4 9h16"/><path d="M9 4v16"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Pixel-perfect copies</h3>
        <p>Page requisites — CSS, JS, fonts and images — are pulled down so the offline copy looks identical to the original.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card" data-reveal>
        <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Links rewritten</h3>
        <p>Every reference is converted to a relative path, so navigation keeps working from any folder on your machine.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card" data-reveal>
        <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg></div>
        <h3>Resumable &amp; resilient</h3>
        <p>Drop your connection? The crawl keeps running server-side and picks up where it left off when you return.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card dark" data-reveal>
        <div>
          <div class="ico"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3v12"/><path d="m7 11 5 5 5-5"/><path d="M5 21h14"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Built for archivists, devs &amp; the curious.</h3>
          <p>Snapshot a portfolio before a redesign, study how a site is built, or keep a reference copy of docs you rely on — all without touching a terminal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="steps-mini">
          <div class="step-mini"><span class="n">↯</span><div><b>Recursive mirror</b><span>--mirror follows the whole tree</span></div></div>
          <div class="step-mini"><span class="n">⇄</span><div><b>Offline link rewrite</b><span>--convert-links for portability</span></div></div>
          <div class="step-mini"><span class="n">⬇</span><div><b>One-click archive</b><span>streamed to you as .zip</span></div></div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

